attachments.title: July 2015 PDX Digital PM Meetup
attachments.text: Who:  PDX Digital PM is Portland&#39;s monthly meetup for Digital PMs and Producers. Account types, strategists, and anyone else interested in the Digital space are welcome as well! When:  July 14th, 2015 from 5:30-7:30PM. What: This month we&#39;re going to mix it up once again, with our host providing the content for the evening. Instrument is going to lead a panel discussion on &#34;Anti-Process,&#34; highlighting how they successfully manage projects in an organization that embraces producers who are creative thinkers and a culture that encourages teams to find &#34;the best approach for the work&#34; rather than relying on fixed processes for everything. You&#39;ll come away from the evening with some takeaways for your own organization and a fascinating look into the slightly different production/project management worldview at Instrument. RSVP today, invite a friend, and we look forward to seeing you there! Where: This month we&#39;ll be returning to Instrument. They first hosted in March 2014 and are excited to host once again. Thank you Instrument!   Why:  Portland&#39;s digital project management/production community is underserved when it comes to sharing knowledge and raising the status of the role industry-wide. Project management for the web is still in its infancy, piecing together elements of agency production, software project management, and digital strategy in a diverse role that requires a great degree of smarts and skill. Let&#39;s get together to share our stories and experiences in an effort to all better manage our projects. Want to know more? Visit <http://pdxdigitalpm.com|pdxdigitalpm.com>
attachments.fallback: Eventbrite: July 2015 PDX Digital PM Meetup
